    <system:String x:Key="UsbModeDemoAdvantage">Sends Valeria=true with the device's native DisplaySize, letting iOS provide a complete phone mirror while remaining in demonstration state. It offers the best compatibility and framing and is recommended for everyday use.</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="UsbModeDemoDisadvantage">iOS enters Apple's demonstration state. The status-bar date, time, and battery are locked to demonstration values instead of the phone's current state.</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="UsbModeDemoNotice">This mode does not enable AirPlay or external playback from video apps.</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="UsbModeAirPlayAdvantage">Sends Valeria=false, uses the device's native size, and retains first-frame probing, orientation detection, and adaptive reconfiguration. Video apps can switch to AirPlay or external playback.</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="UsbModeAirPlayDisadvantage">External-content resolution cannot be guaranteed to adapt perfectly to both the phone and the window. Content may be cropped, use the wrong aspect ratio, or be partly off-screen.</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="UsbModeAirPlayNotice">For custom sizing, click the version in the lower-right corner five times to enable Advanced mode. Custom HPD1 dimensions are risky and can cause a black screen, cropping, or failed USB reconnection.</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="UsbModeAisiAdvantage">Uses an Aisi-style configuration with Valeria=false and a fixed 1565×1565 request, reducing display-negotiation differences between devices.</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="UsbModeAisiDisadvantage">The square target limits source clarity and is unsuitable when image quality is the priority. Landscape content may also be scaled, letterboxed, or shown at an imperfect ratio.</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="UsbModeAisiNotice">This mode does not use this application's native-resolution probing or adaptive orientation reconfiguration.</system:String>
